    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-10-20T05:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-10-20T05:00:00-05:00" n="290"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d290">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">761.93/1737: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gauss</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Chungking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-10-20T17:00:00+07:00"
                            >October 20, 1943—5 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 5:35 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1989. Consul [at] Tihwa reports that oh October 16 he was told by Foreign Affairs
                    delegate that Soviets have fixed price for Toutungho installation at U.S. [$]
                    5,296,600; that formal negotiations not yet undertaken; that 200 of Soviet
                    troops evacuating Hami have stopped at Toutungho and same number are at Tushan;
                    that delegate has protested to local USSR Consul General and that Soviets have
                    withdrawn from Wusu airfield but not from Ining and Toutungho fields. Consul
                    surmises that Soviets intend to retain troops at Toutungho and Tushan until
                    final arrangements for handing over of installations to Chinese are agreed
                    upon.</p>
                <p>Foregoing refers to Embassy’s 1935, October 13 and despatch 1532, September
                        l.<note n="72" xml:id="d290fn72">Latter not printed.</note>
                </p>
                <p>Repeated to Moscow.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Gauss</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
